The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, Aug. 27: The Company Law Board has rejected the petition filed by Zandu Pharmaceuticals opposing the alleged takeover bid by rival Emami, saying that it has no jurisdiction in this issue. Zandu has been warding off a takeover bid by Emami, which acquired a 24 per cent stake in it by buying shares from the Vaidyas.                             
	 New Delhi, Aug. 27: BT Group is planning to sell its 31 per cent stake in Tech Mahindra for an estimated $2 billion. The telecom group may sell all or a large part of its stake in the joint venture, sources close to the development said.                            
	 London, Aug. 27: Oil prices rose for the third day on the back of a possibility that tropical storm Gustav could threaten the Gulf of Mexico oil and gas installations.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 27: Inflation, which has touched a 13-year high of 12.63 per cent, is likely to come down to 5-6 per cent over a peroid of 12 months, chief economic advisor Arvind Virmani said.                             
	 New Delhi, Aug. 27: The BSNL board skipped discussion on its proposed public offer as the company is trying to make the employees union agree to dilution of equity.                                                                                                                             
